VLIB_ORB_getHarrisScore

Detailed Description


Functions

CORBResult VLIB_ORB_getHarrisScore (const CORBParameters *parameters, const CORBInput *input, const CORBOutput *output)

Function Documentation

CORBResult VLIB_ORB_getHarrisScore ( const CORBParameters *  parameters,
const CORBInput *  input,
const CORBOutput *  output 
)

Description:
This function can be called after the fast corners are detected and the Harris Corner Score has been computed from the image. This function simply copies the harris scores associated with each FAST feature from the harris score image (input->harrisImage) to the feature structures (output->harrisResponse) in preparation for next steps.
Parameters:
[in] *parameters The parameters for ORB
[in] *input The input data for ORB - Must be double-word(64-bit) aligned.
[out] *output The output data for ORB - Must be double-word(64-bit) aligned.
Assumptions:
  • Pointer to the input data and output data must be double-word(64-bit) aligned.
  • One of the following FAST corner detectors is run prior to this function:
    • VLIB_afast9_detectCorners
    • VLIB_originalfast9_detectCorners
    • VLIB_afast12_detectCorners
    • VLIB_originalfast12_detectCorners
  • VLIB_harrisScore_7x7 is run before running this function, and the pointer to the harris score output is assigned to the input->harrisImage pointer.
Implementation Notes:
  • This code is compatible with C6XXX fixed point processors.
